The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 28 February is 40,085 (4,639.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 February, there were 698 new confirmed cases (80.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 February, there were 762 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 8% (64 fewer cases).
